{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DdDbjxughzv6jD5FEDF4D6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All pods are healthy. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**Problems found:**\n- `/app` vhost: `app-user` had configure permission empty (only write/read) — client couldn't declare queues/exchanges\n- `/app` vhost: `ops-user` had full permissions — cross-vhost access that shouldn't exist\n- `/ops` vhost: `ops-user` had no permissions at all — ops-client couldn't connect\n\n**Changes made (all via `rabbitmqctl` on `rabbitmq-0`):**\n1. `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — added configure to app-user on /app\n2. `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed ops-user's erroneous /app access\n3. `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted ops-user full access on /ops\n\n**End state:** each user is scoped to exactly its own vhost, both client deployments are `1/1 Running`, and the 3-node cluster remains healthy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":304,"cache_read_input_tokens":32895,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":304},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d410e6a4-48bd-4f8a-9194-5cc1341bba72","uuid":"f38d463d-ba52-4627-b57b-b98724a22fca","request_id":"req_011CcPygpJk2HvfsVJjvqkaC"}
